1. The Complete Presentation Blueprint  

“Act as a professional presentation consultant. Create a complete presentation blueprint for [topic]. Define the objective, target audience, key message, slide flow, and number of slides. Ensure the structure is logical, engaging, and professional.”
2. The Ready-to-Use Slide Deck Generator

“Act as a world-class presentation designer. Create a complete slide-by-slide presentation for [topic] with titles, bullet points, and speaker notes. The slides should be clear, concise, persuasive, and suitable for a professional audience.”
3. The Storytelling Presentation Builder

“Act as a storytelling expert and presentation strategist. Turn [topic] into a compelling narrative presentation. Structure the slides using a storytelling framework (problem → tension → solution → impact). Include engaging slide titles and clear key points.”
4. The TED-Style Presentation Creator

“Act as a TED Talk presentation coach. Create a powerful presentation for [topic] using storytelling, emotional hooks, and memorable takeaways. Each slide should contain minimal text and a strong message designed to captivate an audience.”
5. The Visual Presentation Designer

“Act as a presentation design expert. Create a presentation outline for [topic] and suggest visual ideas for every slide (charts, diagrams, illustrations, comparisons, icons). Focus on making the presentation visually engaging and easy to understand.”
6. The Persuasive Pitch Deck Creator

“Act as a startup pitch deck expert. Create a high-impact pitch presentation about [topic/company/idea] including slides for problem, solution, market opportunity, product, business model, traction, and conclusion. Keep the messaging sharp and persuasive.”
7. The Data-Driven Presentation Builder

“Act as a data visualization expert. Create a data-driven presentation about [topic]. Suggest the best types of charts, graphs, and visual explanations for each slide so complex information becomes easy to understand.”
8. The Presentation Polisher

“Act as a senior presentation consultant. I will provide a presentation topic: [topic]. Create a polished slide structure with powerful slide titles, concise bullet points, and clear speaker notes to make the presentation impactful and memorable.”
💡 Pro tip:
Claude works extremely well if you add this line at the end of the prompt:

“Keep slides concise, professional, and optimized for PowerPoint or Google Slides.”
